VL  - 11
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a response to the 1985 article ?Clustering Countries on Attitudinal Dimensions,? by S. Ronen and O. Shenkar. The author states that the article presents a misleading claim that many areas of Africa have not been studied, and provides a list of studies that prove that research has been done in Africa. The author discusses further general concerns: technocentrism and ethnocentrism in organizational studies. The author gives examples of why he believes countries are only interested in organizational research originating from their own researchers.
AB  - The article presents a response to the 1985 article ?Clustering Countries on Attitudinal Dimensions,? by S. Ronen and O. Shenkar. The author states that the article presents a misleading claim that many areas of Africa have not been studied, and provides a list of studies that prove that research has been done in Africa. The author discusses further general concerns: technocentrism and ethnocentrism in organizational studies. The author gives examples of why he believes countries are only interested in organizational research originating from their own researchers.
