T1  - Measurement of Business Performance in Strategy Research: A Comparison of Approaches
AU  - Venkatraman, N.
AU  - Ramanujam, Vasudevan
Y1  - 1986/10/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1986.4283976
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1986.4283976
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 801
EP  - 814
VL  - 11
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A two-dimensional classificatory scheme highlighting ten different approaches to the measurement of business performance in strategy research is developed. The first dimension concerns the use of financial versus broader operational criteria, while the second focuses on two alternate data sources (primary versus secondary). The scheme permits the classification of an exhaustive coverage of measurement approaches and is useful for discussing their relative merits and demerits. Implications for operationalizing business performance in future strategy research are discussed.
AB  - A two-dimensional classificatory scheme highlighting ten different approaches to the measurement of business performance in strategy research is developed. The first dimension concerns the use of financial versus broader operational criteria, while the second focuses on two alternate data sources (primary versus secondary). The scheme permits the classification of an exhaustive coverage of measurement approaches and is useful for discussing their relative merits and demerits. Implications for operationalizing business performance in future strategy research are discussed.
